commit.message:
Set env variables before starting pytest session

This commit brings back the functionality from version 0.4.0, where
the env variables were set before starting the pytest session. This
behaviour was broken in version 0.5.0 with the below commit:
https://github.com/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/commit/b517a524b5824b0026617b8e182d226f93c906d0
Use pytest fixture to mock "os.environ"
Fix PEP8 in tests
Add missing comma
Add better long description and bump version number
Update version to 0.5.0

commit.message: Add tests for this plugin

Add new option to specify a file with environment variables

A new command line option has been added that will point to a specific file with
environment variables.

It will overwrite anything that it declares and will ignore any .ini settings for this
plugin.
